<title>SWITZERLAND: Ciba details 9-mth sales data.</title>
<headline>Ciba details 9-mth sales data.</headline>
<dateline>BASLE, Switzerland 1996-10-22</dateline>
<text>
<p>Nine months to September 30, 1996</p>
<p>				    (million Sfr unless stated)</p>
<p> Pharmaceuticals		4,399	     up two pct</p>
<p> Self-medication		809		 up three pct</p>
<p> Ciba Vision		    889		 up six pct</p>
<p>    Total Healthcare	  6,097	     up three pct</p>
<p>--</p>
<p> Crop protection		3,482	     up eight pct</p>
<p> Animal health		  580		 up two pct</p>
<p> Seeds			    213		 up 22 pct</p>
<p>    Total Agriculture	 4,275	     up eight pct</p>
<p>--</p>
<p> Textile dyes		   868		 up five pct</p>
<p> Chemicals			815		 up five pct</p>
<p> Additives			1,551	     dn four pct</p>
<p> Pigments			 802		 up one pct</p>
<p> Polymers			 987		 up six pct</p>
<p>Total Industry</p>
<p>(without composites, Mettler</p>
<p>Toledo, leather business)   4,934	     up one pct</p>
<p>--</p>
<p> Composites		     105		 dn 65 pct</p>
<p> Mettler Toledo		 762		 up three pct</p>
<p>    Total Industry	    5,890	     dn two pct</p>
<p>--</p>
<p>    Total group		 16,262	    up two pct</p>
<p>Note - Chemical segment growth rate shown excludes figures of group's leather businesss. The corresponding sales figures amounts to 726 million Swiss francs.</p>
<p>Composite sector sales in most countries deconsolidated due to combination of composites business with Hexcel Corp.</p>
<p>-- Zurich Editorial +41 1 631 7340</p>
